38320-1}}\n** Volume 2: ''Research Methods in Psychology''. John A. Schinka & Wayne F. Velicer, eds. {{ISBN|0-471-38513-1}}\n** Volume 3: ''Biological Psychology''. Michela Gallagher & Randy J. Nelson, eds. {{ISBN|0-471-38403-8}}\n** Volume 4: ''Experimental Psychology''. Alice F. Healy & Robert W. Proctor, eds. {{ISBN|0-471-39262-6}}\n** Volume 8: ''Clinical Psychology''. George Stricker, Thomas A. Widiger, eds. {{ISBN|0-471-39263-4}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{Library resources box|onlinebooks=yes}}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.03136-6 |chapter=Nature-Nurture Controversy, History of |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=340\u2013344 |year=2015 |last1=Badcock |first1=Christopher R. |isbn=9780080970875 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.22007-2 |chapter=Industrial\u2013Organizational Psychology: Science and Practice |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=879\u2013884 |year=2015 |last1=Cascio |first1=Wayne F. |isbn=9780080970875 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.24095-6 |chapter=Social Psychology |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=532\u2013537 |year=2015 |last1=Chryssochoou |first1=Xenia |isbn=9780080970875 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.27049-9 |chapter=Philosophy, Psychiatry, and Psychology |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=31\u201336 |year=2015 |last1=Deakin |first1=Nicholas |isbn=9780080970875 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.92147-0 |chapter=Intelligence in Cultural, Social and Educational Context |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=313\u2013322 |year=2015 |last1=Demetriou |first1=Andreas |isbn=9780080970875 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.21073-8 |chapter=Counseling Psychology |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |p